'''SpARCS1049+56''' is a [[galaxy cluster]] whose heart is bursting with new stars and located at a distance of about 9.8 billion light-years away from [[Earth]]. It was discovered by [[NASA|NASA's]] [[Hubble Space Telescope|Hubble]] and [[Spitzer Space Telescope|Spitzer]] space telescopes on 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|title = NASA Telescopes Find Galaxy Cluster with Vibrant Heart|url = http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?feature=4715|website = www.jpl.nasa.gov|accessdate = 2015-09-18}}</ref>

